British Election Study variables

Evan Odell

2017-08-01

Variable names in census_11

Due to the 191 variables included in the census_11 dataset, including information on each variable in the parlitools reference manual is very lengthy and not very user friendly. This vignette reproduces the table including with the British Election Study data, available here. The ‘Name’ column refers to the variable name used in the bes_2015 dataset, the ‘Data Type’ column refers to the R data type, and the ‘Census Table’ column refers to the location in the 2011 Census that demographic data was retrieved from.
